&lt;p&gt;Care Group Support Manager – Division of Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AfC Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Walsall Healthcare NHS Trust is an integrated provider of community and hospital health care and the Division of Surgery have an exciting opportunity available for a motivated and experienced individual for the role of Care Group Support Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a proactive individual with excellent leadership skills who has the aptitude to facilitate and effect change. You will contribute to the development of services in the Care Group, in particular focusing on delivering waiting time performance standards (Referral to treatment and Cancer standards).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support the Care Group Manager/Deputy Divisional Director of Operations who in conjunction with the Clinical Director and Matron are responsible for delivery and management of all aspects of the Care Group including quality, performance, finance and workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are up for a challenge and can demonstrate the skills outlined in the job description and person specification then we would like to hear from you. For an informal discussion please contact Jayne Cox, Deputy Director of Corporate Services on 01922 656353.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJayne CoxEmail addressjayne.cox@walsallhealthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number01922 656353Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
